biolockj.util.r

Class PlotScript

  • java.lang.Object
    • biolockj.util.r.PlotScript

  • public class PlotScript
extends Object
    This utility generates the standard R code functions needed to display graphics in our PDF reports.

      • rFunctionAddPlotLabel

        protected String rFunctionAddPlotLabel()
        The method returns R code for the function "addPlotLabel"( label, size, color, las, side, rowIndex, colIndex ). This R function adds the label to the page using the mtext() function based on the orientation parameters. The PDF prints up to 4 plots per page, with the plot label oriented along the Y-axis of each plot.

        R Function parameters:

        • label = Format this value in bold with R function bquote(bold(.( label )))
        • size = Set size of label via mtext(... cex=size, ...)
        • color = Set color of label via mtext(... col=color, ...)
        • las = Set text orientation via mtext(... las=las, ...) with options 1 (for HORIZONTAL) or 3 (for VERTICAL)
        • side = Set mtext(... side=side, ...) with options 2 (for LEFT_SIDE) or 3 (for TOP_SIDE)
        • rowIndex = Set mtext(... adj=rowIndex, ...) to adjust label orientation right to left
        • colIndex = Set mtext(... line=colIndex, ...) to adjust label orientation top to bottom
        Returns:
        R code

      • rFunctionGetColor

        protected String rFunctionGetColor()
                            throws Exception
        The method returns R code for the function "getColor"( v ). If any P-value in vector (v) is equal to or below the configured "r.pvalCutoff" return "r.colorHighlight", otherwise return "r.colorBase".

        R Function parameters:

        • v = Vector of P-values

        Required Config properties: "r.pvalCutoff", "r.colorHighlight", "r.colorBase".

        Returns:
        R code
        Throws:
        Exception - if Config property is missing or invalid

      • rFunctionGetLabels

        protected String rFunctionGetLabels()
                             throws Exception
        This method returns R code for the function "getLabels"(labels).
        Method returns the list of given labels as is if to be written horizontally. For vertical labels, return labels after trimming excessive characters for display purposes. The max length of vertical labels = 5.

        R Function parameter: labels = Vector of labels to print on plot axis

        BioLockJ R function called by this method: getLas(labels)

        Returns:
        R code
        Throws:
        Exception - if Config error occurs

      • rFunctionGetLas

        protected String rFunctionGetLas()
        This method returns R code for the function "getLas"(labels).
        Method checks total number of characters for all labels to determine if they will fit written horizontally. If so, return global R script constant HORIZONTAL, otherwise, return global R script constant VERTICAL.
        Returns:
        R code
